    "plan_content": "Here's a summary of the plan I've created, based on thorough exploration of the codebase with exact line numbers verified:\n\n---\n\n## Plan: 7 steps across 4 files, zero new imports\n\n### What I found\n- All required packages (`errtypes`, `manifest`, `model`, `os`, `io`, `fmt`, `errors`) are **already imported** in `server/routes.go`\n- The `RenameHandler` follows the `CopyHandler` + `DeleteHandler` patterns exactly\n- Every exact insertion point was confirmed against real line numbers\n\n### The 7 steps\n\n| Step | File | What | Where |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| 1 | `api/types.go` | Add `RenameRequest` struct | After line 765 (`CopyRequest` end) |\n| 2 | `api/client.go` | Add `Client.Rename()` method | After line 387 (`Copy()` end) |\n| 3 | `server/routes.go` | Add `RenameHandler` method | After line 1483 (`CopyHandler` end) |\n| 4 | `server/routes.go` | Register `/api/rename` route | After line 1698 (`/api/copy` route) |\n| 5 | `cmd/cmd.go` | Add `RenameHandler` func | After line 1350 (`CopyHandler` end) |\n| 6 | `cmd/cmd.go` | Add `renameCmd` cobra command | After line 2263 (`copyCmd` end) |\n| 7 | `cmd/cmd.go` | Register `renameCmd` in `AddCommand` | After line 2345 (`copyCmd,`) |\n\n### Key design decisions in `RenameHandler`\n1. **Empty checks before `ParseName`** — gives explicit `\"source is required\"` errors rather than a generic parse failure\n2. **409 via `manifest.ParseNamedManifest(dst) == nil`** — same approach `DeleteHandler` uses to confirm existence\n3. **Delete via `m.Remove()` + `m.RemoveLayers()`** — mirrors `DeleteHandler` exactly; if delete fails after copy, returns 500 (copy succeeded, caller can retry delete)\n4. **No `getExistingName()` call** — not required per spec; `CopyModel` and `manifest.ParseNamedManifest` operate directly on the parsed names",
